description:
Daredevil's life is in tatters - his best friend thinks he's insane, and he's starting to think he might be right! An impossible crime leads DD into a clash with a deadly enemy...

By Mark Waid and Chris Samnee!

Also: The Avengers Academy is closed, and the students are on their own! But an old enemy is back, with sinister plans for the world!

By Christos Gage, Tom Grummett and Andrea Di Vito!

Plus: Drax the Destroyer is targeted by alien assassins! Don't miss a special prelude to 'Guardians of the Galaxy'!

By Brian Michael Bendis and Michael Avon Oeming!

deck: Condition Cryptical #2: The Road, from DeadZone Comics
description: Cliff and his family are on their way, making a road trip to the beach for a family getaway…but then there’s a problem: traffic on the regular route is backed up for hours. In a last ditch effort to get to the beach in decent time, Cliff takes an alternate route on a remote, secluded road to bypass the backed-up traffic. But once on “The Road” things quickly go from bad to worse when very odd, inexplicable events start to unfold…and Cliff starts to drift off into madness…or does he?
name: The Road

person_credits.name: Fernando Jimenez
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, inker, colorist, cover

deck: Elementis Special Operations Unit #2: Confronting Demons, from DeadZone Comics.
description: James Huddro is dying from inexplicable causes, and his friend, William Aether, insists that the only way of saving his life is administering treatment that would kill anyone else. Tensions increase between Dr. LaVosier and his daughter, Terrah, in light of revelations brought about by Aether’s mysterious connection with a source of mystical knowledge that he identifies as “The Stream.” Meanwhile, Ignise continues to struggle with her unique ability, trying to understand if it’s a gift of nature…or a curse of fate. Amidst the turmoil unfolding at the Elementis Compound, word has reached Dr. LaVosier that an amateur paranormal researcher has died during an investigation, but the circumstances surrounding his death can only be described as highly suspicious. Experience has taught Dr. LaVosier that accepting what is considered logical and conventional not only prevents discovery…it can be deadly, especially when it involves confronting demons. Join the team as they embark on an adventure that will either bring them together as the world’s premier supernatural-science special operations unit…or break them apart.
name: Confronting Demons

volume.name: Now and Then Presents Oktoberfest Comics

description: Betty and Veronica may be BFFs, but they're not the only ones! Riverdale's also home to a bunch of guys who pal around and watch each other's backs. Archie and Jughead, Moose and Dilton, Reggie and... Reggie..? These dynamic duos are so off-the-wall they have to be seen to be believed! Hang out with the boys in this 100-page digital exclusive book and see why these best friends are the best!

Collects Inhumans (2003) #1-12.

The next generation of Inhumans star in this atmospheric ensemble drama, collected for the first time in one trade paperback! They're just ordinary exchange students from a far-off land, here to learn about our culture - except their home is a mysterious city on the moon, and they each possess fabulous, exotic abilities and appearances. The product of experiments on humanity by an alien culture millennia ago, the Inhumans are a race governed by the laws of genetics. Here as nowhere else, diversity and individuality are prized beyond compare. The Inhumans have flourished in isolation from humanity within their kingdom of Attilan on the surface of the moon, but what happens when their king decides to send some of his subjects to Earth to learn about humans? Will they be able to integrate into human culture? More important, will they even try?
name: TPB

description:
TRAUMA

Nominated for an AASC Publishing Award and an Association of Arts & Social Change People's Choice Award, Hobson's Gate tells the story of a homicide detective battling personal and, what may be, real demons in his city.

While losing ground on the most brutal murders Southtale Gate has ever seen, Detective Joseph Hobson begins to lose his mind. In the span of a week there are dozens of bodies, massed together in a frozen pile of slaughter. With no evidence to speak of, even the messages in blood left at the scenes present more questions than they answer. As fatigue, depression and frustration set in, Hobson seems to be losing on both fronts: within the walls of his city, and within his mind.

Can Hobson fight back his own demons and save the people from the worst killing his force has seen? Or will he succumb to the broken record of his mind, and let these demons take him down...and city along with it?

Hobson's Gate Trauma is the first book of a three book series including Trauma, Pressure and Descent.

Following the craziness from last issue, Justin realizes that he must do what ever hero would do,help the stranger rescue his son.Buy doing this he discovers a secret about the stranger that has a past of his own.Will Justin continue the rescue?Can he team up with this man ,or will his secret be to much for him to bear?Find out in the next exciting issue of the Comic Bug!
name: Comic Bug
